Subject: rPSA-2009-0091-1 cyrus-sasl cyrus-sasl-server

rPath Security Advisory: 2009-0091-1
Published: 2009-05-27
Products:
    rPath Appliance Platform Linux Service 1
    rPath Appliance Platform Linux Service 2
    rPath Linux 1
    rPath Linux 2

Rating: Critical
Exposure Level Classification:
    Remote Root Deterministic Unauthorized Access
Updated Versions:
    cyrus-sasl=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1/2.1.21-5.3-1
    cyrus-sasl=conary.rpath.com@rpl:2/2.1.22-7.1-1
    cyrus-sasl-server=conary.rpath.com@rpl:2/2.1.22-7.1-1

rPath Issue Tracking System:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-3044

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2009-0688

Description:
    Previous versions of the cyrus-sasl package contain a buffer overflow
    error that may allow remote (unauthenticated) attackers to execute
    arbitrary code.

